  "body": {
    "type": "doc",
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "A slab-built wall vase is constructed from flat clay panels cut at angles and joined so the front face leans forward from the back. The angled front is the design element: it creates a dynamic profile when the vase is seen from the side. No kiln is needed. The vase holds dried flowers directly, or a small glass insert for fresh stems."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "suppliesCard",
        "attrs": {
          "heading": "What you need",
          "items": [
            {
              "name": "Air-dry clay",
              "quantity": "600 g",
              "substitution": "Paper clay for stronger joins"
            },
            {
              "name": "Pottery rolling pin",
              "quantity": "1",
              "substitution": null
            },
            {
              "name": "Fettling knife",
              "quantity": "1",
              "substitution": null
            },
            {
              "name": "Needle tool",
              "quantity": "1",
              "substitution": null
            },
            {
              "name": "Wooden rib",
              "quantity": "1",
              "substitution": null
            },
            {
              "name": "Wooden board",
              "quantity": "1",
              "substitution": null
            },
            {
              "name": "Set square or card template",
              "quantity": "1",
              "substitution": null
            }
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Panel plan"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The vase has five panels cut from a rolled "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                "attrs": {
                  "termSlug": "slab"
                }
              }
            ],
            "text": "slab"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " at 8 mm thick. Cut to the following dimensions:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Back wall: 80 mm wide, 180 mm tall (rectangle)"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Front wall: 80 mm wide, 160 mm tall (rectangle; shorter than the back so the front leans forward)"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Two side walls: 60 mm wide, cut as trapezoids: 180 mm tall at the back edge, 160 mm tall at the front edge"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Base: 80 mm x 60 mm (rectangle). Pierce two drainage holes with the needle tool"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Assembly"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "1. Join back wall to base"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                "attrs": {
                  "termSlug": "score-and-slip"
                }
              }
            ],
            "text": "Score and slip"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " the bottom edge of the back wall and the back edge of the base. Press together at 90 degrees. Reinforce the interior seam with a thin clay coil and smooth flat with the rib."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "2. Attach the side walls"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Score and slip the back and base edges of each side wall and the corresponding faces on the back wall and base. Press each side wall into place so the taller back edge aligns with the back wall and the shorter front edge will align with the front wall once it is added. Reinforce all interior seams."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "3. Add the front wall"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Score and slip the front edges of both side walls and both side edges of the front wall. Press the front wall into place. The front wall is shorter than the back, so the top of the vase is open at an angle, slanting from the front rim toward the back rim. Score and slip the bottom edge of the front wall and the front edge of the base, then press together."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Reaching leather-hard"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Let the assembled vase stiffen under a plastic tent until "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                "attrs": {
                  "termSlug": "leather-hard"
                }
              }
            ],
            "text": "leather-hard"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " (one to two hours). Then refine the external seams with the rib and the needle tool: smooth any excess clay at the corners, and compress the rim edges."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Drying and finishing"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Dry fully to "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                "attrs": {
                  "termSlug": "bone-dry"
                }
              }
            ],
            "text": "bone-dry"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " over two to three days under a loose plastic tent. Sand smooth, paint with acrylics, and seal with two coats of PVA. For fresh flowers, drop a small glass or plastic tube inside before filling with water."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Variations"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Carve a simple pattern into the front panel before assembling the vase."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Make three vases at different heights and mount them at staggered levels on the wall."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Add a hanging hole through the back wall before drying by piercing the slab with a 5 mm dowel when the clay is leather-hard."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "troubleshooter",
        "attrs": {
          "heading": "Wall-vase problems",
          "intro": null,
          "items": [
            {
              "symptom": "Corners pull apart as vase dries",
              "cause": "Side walls applied to partially dry back and base; shrinkage rates differ",
              "fix": "Assemble all five panels in one session while all slabs are equally fresh. Score and reinforce all interior seams"
            },
            {
              "symptom": "Angled opening gaps unevenly",
              "cause": "Side walls were not cut to matching trapezoid dimensions",
              "fix": "Make a card template for the side walls and use it to cut both identically"
            }
          ]
        }
      }
    ]
  }
}